name: Stacey Lee
text: What a wonderful experience! Rob was very friendly and knowledgable.  The blueberries were delicious as well.  I used google maps to find the place, no problem

name: mike murphy
text:
Sweet Fresh Blue Berries
Plentiful Ripe Berries

name: Rebecca Palmer
text: We went today and picked all we wanted of the sweetest juiciest blueberries I've ever seen. Only $10 a gallon! We loved it, and had absolutely no problem in contacting the owner anytime we called. Very nice man, helpful and quite knowledgeable. Acres and acres of beautiful, chemical free berries, but hurry before the season is over!

name: Kevin Flamm
text: We love this place. We live in Philadelphia and visit Dadeville every year. This farm is part of our annual pilgrimage. There are 35 acres of pesticide-free blueberries. The owner is very pleasant to deal with. If you are lucky, you will run into a man who works at this farm. His name is Jeremiah. He showed us the best places to pick, and what to look for in a blueberry. I have to say, speaking with Jeremiah was the highlight of my visit!  Thank you to my new friend!

name: Sandra Price
text: Good large berries, sweet taste. Much cheaper than the grocery store. Nice people.

name: Amy Nichols
text: It was not very good place. Can never get ahold of anyone and it just isn't very amusing

name: Barry K
text: We picked late/end of season (first week of July) and got some great fruit. There was a little bit of shaded picking available which was a nice treat. Bring some bug spray with you for mosquitos!

name: Lisa Bailey
text: Easy picking blueberries. There are a lot of bushes and it is easy to get to and the berries have always been really good. We've been going here for 3 years now. The family is really nice to work with. Be honest and if no-one is home they have a mail box to put your money in. Again please be honest, they are really great people! 😀  The parking is good and they have lots of space. You don't have to walk too far to get to the bushes. It is down a little decline, but it is gradual.

name: RAFI SAZZAD
text: You can handpick the blueberry and bring with you for a cheaper price!
